President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Yogi Berra. He described Berra as an American original, a Hall of Famer, and a humble veteran. The president praised Berra's sense of humor and his ability to make predictions. He also highlighted Berra's qualities as a sportsman and a citizen, including his big heart, competitive spirit, and his desire to make baseball accessible to everyone. The president offered his deepest condolences to Berra's family, friends, and fans in New York and around the world.